From 55fb30d049114f31abbc3c1a176334555e8d788b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chronium <chronium@interlink.local>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 14:24:10 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] chronium: virtualize WebGL surface (getParameter MAX_* /
 ranges + getShaderPrecisionFormat) per profile

Real Chrome's UNMASKED_RENDERER_WEBGL is cross-checked by CreepJS / iphey
/ PixelScan against the behavioral GPU surface: MAX_TEXTURE_SIZE,
MAX_VERTEX_UNIFORM_VECTORS, MAX_VIEWPORT_DIMS, ALIASED_LINE_WIDTH_RANGE,
shader precision triples. Spoofing only the renderer string still loses
to 'claims RTX 3060 but MAX_VERTEX_UNIFORM_VECTORS=1024 (= Intel iGPU)'.

This patch virtualizes the full param surface from the profile JSON so
the entire WebGL fingerprint is internally coherent with the claimed
renderer.

Plumbing follows the established pattern (patches 0011, 0015, 0018):
- chrome_switches.{h,cc}: new kFingerprintWebGLParams switch.
- fingerprint_profile.{h,cc}: WebGLParamsBlob() walks the profile's
  webgl.params dict (int / [int,int] / [float,float]) and
  webgl.shader_precision dict ({shader-hex: {precision-hex: triple}})
  into a TSV blob; chrome_content_browser_client appends hex-encoded.
- chrome_content_renderer_client.cc: decodes hex + feeds
  FingerprintState::SetWebGLParams.
- fingerprint_state.{h,cc}: SetWebGLParams parser + 4 typed accessors
  (WebGLIntParam, WebGLIntRangeParam, WebGLFloatRangeParam,
  WebGLShaderPrecision) with sentinel returns when not pinned so the
  WebGL getParameter switch falls through unchanged.
- webgl_rendering_context_base.cc::getParameter early-returns spoofed
  values before any GL roundtrip. Sentinels: -1 for int, INT32_MIN
  for int range, -1.0f for float range.
- webgl_rendering_context_base.cc::getShaderPrecisionFormat early-
  returns the pinned triple; sentinel precision=-1 means fall through.

Profile schema additions:
  webgl.params: { '0x0D33': 16384, '0x0D3A': [32768, 32768],
                  '0x846E': [1.0, 1.0], ... }
  webgl.shader_precision: { '0x8B31': { '0x8DF0': [127,127,23], ... },
                            '0x8B30': { ... } }

The 170 bundled JSONs were enriched via scripts/enrich-webgl-params.py
with vendor-appropriate values:
  NVIDIA/AMD discrete: MAX_VERTEX_UNIFORM_VECTORS=4095, MAX_VIEWPORT=[32768,32768]
  Intel iGPU: MAX_VERTEX_UNIFORM_VECTORS=1024, MAX_VIEWPORT=[16384,16384]
  Intel HD2500/3000: MAX_TEXTURE_SIZE=8192
  ANGLE D3D11 shader precision: same triples across vendors (HLSL compiler-set)
